{{More citations needed|date=August 2007}}{{Update|date=January 2018}}{{Infobox website | name = Search Engine Watch | logo = SearchEngineWatch.gif | logo_size = 250px | logocaption = | screenshot = | collapsible = | collapsetext = | caption = | url = {{URL|https://searchenginewatch.com}} | slogan = | commercial = | type = | registration = | language = English | num_users = | content_license = | content_licence = | programming language = | owner = Blenheim Chalcot | author = [[Danny Sullivan (technologist)|Danny Sullivan]] | editor = Rebecca Sentance | launch_date = {{Start date and age|1996|df=no}} | alexa = | revenue = | current_status = | footnotes = }} '''Search Engine Watch''' (SEW) provides news and information about [[search engines]] and [[search engine marketing]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/01/28/technology/the-crumbs-you-leave-behind.html|title=The Crumbs You Leave Behind|last=Mitchell|first=Dan|date=2006|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-01-05|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>
Search Engine Watch was started by [[Danny Sullivan (technologist)|Danny Sullivan]] in 1996. In 1997, Sullivan sold it for an undisclosed amount to [[WebMediaBrands|MecklerMedia]] (now WebMediaBrands). In 2005 the website and related [[Search Engine Strategies]] conference series were sold to [[Incisive Media]] for $43 million. On November 30, 2006, Danny Sullivan left Search Engine Watch, after his resignation announcement on August 29, 2006.<ref>[http://blog.searchenginewatch.com/blog/060829-063058 Stepping Down From Search Engine Watch] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060901115553/http://blog.searchenginewatch.com/blog/060829-063058 |date=2006-09-01 }}</ref> Rebecca Lieb was named editor-in-chief the following month.
In 2015, Incisive Media sold [[Search Engine Strategies|SES]], Search Engine Watch, and [[ClickZ]] to Blenheim Chalcot.<ref>{{Cite web| title = Incisive Media's ClickZ, SES & Search Engine Watch Acquired By Blenheim Chalcot| work = Marketing Land| accessdate = 2015-05-06| url = http://marketingland.com/incisive-medias-clickz-ses-and-sew-acquired-by-london-based-blenheim-chalcot-125871}}</ref>
[[Google]]'s [[Matt Cutts]] has called Search Engine Watch "a must read." [[Yahoo]]'s Tim Mayer has said that it is the "most authoritative source on search."<ref>{{cite news|publisher=usatoday.com|accessdate=2007-08-30|date=August 1, 2006|title=Got a search engine question? Ask Mr. Sullivan|url=https://www.usatoday.com/money/industries/technology/2006-08-01-sullivan-search_x.htm | first=Jefferson | last=Graham}}</ref>
